---

# Step 1 вҖ” User sends a request

A controller (or Swagger UI, Postman, MQTT client) sends a USP request.

Example:

```json
{
  "Operation":"GetDevice"
}
```

or

```json
{
  "Operation":"Operate",
  "Command":"Ping",
  "Arguments":{
      "Host":"8.8.8.8"
  }
}
```

---

# Step 2 вҖ” FastAPI receives the request

The request reaches

```
POST /usp
```

implemented in

```
tr369/api.py
```

It simply forwards the JSON to

```
USPMessageProcessor
```

---

# Step 3 вҖ” USPMessageProcessor

This is the heart of TR-369.

It

* Parses JSON
* Validates it
* Creates USPRequest
* Determines the operation

Example

```
Operation = Get
```

вҶ“

calls

```
controller.get_parameter()
```

Example

```
Operation = Operate
```

вҶ“

calls

```
controller.operate()
```

---

# Step 4 вҖ” USPController

Controller is the interface between

```
MessageProcessor
```

and

```
USPAgent
```

It doesn't execute logic.

It forwards everything.

Example

```
operate()

вҶ“

agent.operate()
```

---

# Step 5 вҖ” USPAgent

USPAgent represents the router.

It owns

```
GetHandler

SetHandler

OperateHandler

SubscriptionManager

NotifyHandler

SessionManager
```

Depending on request

```
Get

вҶ“

GetHandler
```

or

```
Operate

вҶ“

OperateHandler
```

---

# Step 6 вҖ” Handlers

Each USP command has its own handler.

Examples

```
GetHandler

reads TR181
```

```
OperateHandler

runs commands
```

```
SubscriptionManager

stores subscriptions
```

```
NotifyHandler

creates notifications
```

---

# Step 7 вҖ” TR181Mapper

Suppose request is

```
GetDevice
```

USPAgent calls

```
TR181Mapper
```

Mapper builds

```
Device
```

from multiple classes

```
DeviceInfo

IP

Routing
```

Produces

```
Device
 в”ңв”Җв”Җ DeviceInfo
 в”ңв”Җв”Җ IP
 в””в”Җв”Җ Routing
```

---

# Step 8 вҖ” RouterService

RouterService actually communicates with Ubuntu.

Example

```
hostname()

вҶ“

SSH

вҶ“

hostname command
```

Example

```
routes()

вҶ“

ip route
```

Example

```
memory()

вҶ“

cat /proc/meminfo
```

---

# Step 9 вҖ” SSHClient

SSHClient uses Paramiko

```
Windows

вҶ“

SSH

вҶ“

Ubuntu VM
```

Commands like

```
hostname

uptime

ip addr

ip route

cat /proc/cpuinfo
```

are executed remotely.

---

# Step 10 вҖ” Ubuntu executes Linux command

Ubuntu returns

Example

```
hostname
```

вҶ“

```
usp-router
```

Example

```
uptime
```

вҶ“

```
39192.11 20100.44
```

---

# Step 11 вҖ” Response travels back

Ubuntu

вҶ“

SSHClient

вҶ“

RouterService

вҶ“

TR181

вҶ“

USPAgent

вҶ“

USPController

вҶ“

MessageProcessor

вҶ“

HTTP Response

---

# Operate Flow

Example

```
Operate

вҶ“

Ping

вҶ“

OperateHandler

вҶ“

RouterService

вҶ“

SSH

вҶ“

ping 8.8.8.8

вҶ“

Ubuntu

вҶ“

Output

вҶ“

JSON
```

---

# Subscribe Flow

```
Subscribe

вҶ“

SubscriptionManager

вҶ“

stores

DeviceBoot
```

Later

```
Notify

вҶ“

checks

DeviceBoot exists

вҶ“

NotifyHandler

вҶ“

Notification
```

---

# Session Flow

```
Session

вҶ“

SessionManager

вҶ“

UUID

вҶ“

Agent ID

вҶ“

Controller ID

вҶ“

Created Time

вҶ“

Response
```

Heartbeat

```
Heartbeat

вҶ“

SessionManager

вҶ“

Alive
```

Disconnect

```
Disconnect

вҶ“

Connected=False
```

---

# MQTT Flow

```
Windows Controller

вҶ“

MQTT Publish

вҶ“

Mosquitto Broker (Ubuntu)

вҶ“

mqtt_listener.py

вҶ“

USPMessageProcessor

вҶ“

USPController

вҶ“

USPAgent

вҶ“

TR181

вҶ“

RouterService

вҶ“

SSH

вҶ“

Ubuntu

вҶ“

Response

вҶ“

mqtt_client.py

вҶ“

Mosquitto

вҶ“

Controller
```

---

# Complete Data Flow

```text
Controller
     в”Ӯ
HTTP / MQTT
     в”Ӯ
USP API
     в”Ӯ
USPMessageProcessor
     в”Ӯ
USPController
     в”Ӯ
USPAgent
     в”Ӯ
Handlers
     в”Ӯ
TR181Mapper
     в”Ӯ
RouterService
     в”Ӯ
SSHClient
     в”Ӯ
Ubuntu Router
     в”Ӯ
Linux Commands
     в”Ӯ
Results
     в”Ӯ
JSON Response
```

---

# Technologies Used

| Layer                | Technology     |
| -------------------- | -------------- |
| Backend API          | FastAPI        |
| Remote Communication | Paramiko (SSH) |
| Router OS            | Ubuntu VM      |
| Device Model         | TR-181         |
| Management Protocol  | TR-369 USP     |
| Messaging            | JSON           |
| MQTT Broker          | Mosquitto      |
| MQTT Client          | paho-mqtt      |
| Language             | Python 3.11    |

---

## In summary

Your project demonstrates a **USP Agent** that exposes a **TR-181 device model**. It accepts management requests over **HTTP (FastAPI)** and **MQTT (Mosquitto)**, processes them through the TR-369 layers (`USPMessageProcessor` вҶ’ `USPController` вҶ’ `USPAgent`), retrieves or modifies device information via the TR-181 model, executes Linux commands on an Ubuntu VM over SSH when needed, and returns standardized JSON responses. This mirrors the layered architecture used in TR-369 implementations, while using simplified handlers and JSON messages instead of the full USP protocol encoding.
